Aaron stated the spill looks to be contained to the box it is packaged in and is still in the trailer but may h ave spilled on the trailer floor as well.~~~

The shipment discovered wet because it was leaked on by another shipmet containg a non hazardous cleaner. Upon opening the brown outer box, it was discovered to contain 2 Black boxes "Marz Distribution, UN1070 Nitrous Oxide 99.0%, UN4GY/15/S/24/CNC297205." Inside of the 2 boxes were 2 smaller boxes that contained 1 cylinder @ 1364 grams. The smaller boxes are marked with the same MFG information , UN#, PSN, Hazard Labels 2.2 NFG and 5.1 Oxidizer. Total of 4 Cylinders-marked with the same mfg and hazard information and the wording "Adult Only 18+, Do Not Inhale, Not For Medical Use, Non refillable, Do Not Inhale, Nitrous Oxide Food and Beverage Additive." There was NO RELEASE. The shipment is being held for FAA investigation.

The SDS on these two items show that they should be regulated and the inner box that the BioFreeze is in has a limited quantity diamond on it.  These items did not leak.  A unregulated bottle of ProteX disinfectant has a crack in it and leaked in the box.

column169: On September 4, 2024, one (1) 5-gallon pail of printer ink was damaged in transit and released approximately two (2) gallons of product to the trailer interior. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from HazChem Environmental (HCE) to remediate the impacted site.  HCE personnel utilized hand tools and absorbents to remediate the printing ink-impacted trailer floor. All impacted material was collected and containerized into two (2) 55-gallon drums and staged on site for transport and disposal.

column169: During unloading operations at the Menomonee Falls 10-Day Facility, staff discovered a leak from a 5-gallon container of lithium preserved in mineral oil inside a trailer. The spill was limited to less than 2 gallons and remained confined within the trailer. Upon investigation, it was determined that the leak occurred due to improper securing of the load, which allowed the containers to shift during transportation. The spill was remediated by trained Veolia personnel and the container was properly closed.
column170: Veolia management will review with employees the importance of load securement, proper closure, and to use the proper containers for the waste.

column43: LITHIUM ION BATTERIES CONTAINED IN EQUIPMENT INCLUDING LITHIUM ION POLYMER BATTERIES
column169: On September 3rd a package was discovered during a basic package inspection process that contained batteries.   There were no markings on the outside of the package indicating a battery was inside.After opening the package it was discovered that it contained a drill and 2 lithium ion batteries that powered the drill.  The package is being held pending disposition.

On 9/6/2024 at approximately 1115, Dangerous Goods Administration received a call from Employee 3962724 at the sort facility in Aguadilla, Puerto Rico, reporting undeclared dangerous goods.  The shipment consisted of several packages appearing to be processed through Amazon.   Spillage occurred among the packages, prompting FedEx to further investigate, resulting in the identification of the spilled package as nail polish remover, which was not prepared in accordance with IATA Regulations, missing the required markings, labeling, packaging and paperwork.  Dangerous Goods Administration obtained the safety data sheet of a similar product to verify indentification.   The other packages remain unopened and the contents unknown.   The spilled package was removed from the box and the remainder of the shipment is being held for package retreival.
